    <introduction>
        <p>
            Let's revisit the proof of <xref ref="thm-area-parabola"/>, where we showed that the planar region <me>U \defn \set{(x,y) \in \R^2}{0 \leq x \leq 1,\,0 \leq y \leq x^2}</me> had area <m>\frac{1}{3}</m>
        </p>
    </introduction>

    <subsection xml:id="subsec-upper-lower-sums">
        <title>Upper and lower sums</title>
        <definition xml:id="def-partition">
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Let <m>a \lt b</m>. 
                    A <term>partition</term> of the closed interval <m>[a,b]</m> is a finite ordered list of numbers <m>(t_0,t_1,\cdots,t_N)</m>, such that <m>t_0 = a</m>, <m>t_n = b</m>, and <m>t_i \lt t_{i+1}</m> for all <m>0 \leq i \leq N-1</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </definition>

    </subsection>

